Weeks 1 to 2 are your foundation phase. Use conservative loads and focus entirely on learning each movement. Aim for RPE 6 to 7. 
Weeks 3 and 4 are your build phase, increase load by the smallest available increment where technique is solid and aim for RPE 7 to 8. Weeks 5 and 6 are your progression phase, increase load further and aim for the lower end of each rep range. Weeks 7 and 8 are your consolidation phase, push your working sets harder, aiming for RPE 8 to 9.

Progressive overload rule: when you can complete all sets and reps with 2 or more reps remaining in the tank, increase the load by the smallest available increment at the next session.', 'functional_strength', 'full_gym', 56, 8, 'beginner', '', '{full_body}', '2026-02-22 15:31:42.078021', 2, NULL, 'main', 'manual', NULL, '{gym}');

Weeks 1 and 2 are your foundation phase. Use conservative loads and focus on learning each movement, aiming for RPE 6 to 7. Weeks 3 and 4 are your build phase. Increase load by the smallest available increment where technique is solid, aiming for RPE 7 to 8. Weeks 5 and 6 are your progression phase. Increase load further and aim for the lower end of each rep range. Weeks 7 and 8 are your consolidation phase. Push working sets harder, aiming for RPE 8 to 9.

Progressive overload rule: when you complete all sets and reps with 2 or more reps remaining in the tank, increase the load by the smallest available increment at the next session.', 'functional_strength', 'full_gym', 56, 8, 'beginner', '', '{full_body,beginner}', '2026-02-23 09:32:15.142321', 2, NULL, 'strength', 'manual', NULL, '{gym}');

Weeks 1 and 2 are your foundation phase. Use a lighter band and focus on learning each movement, aiming for RPE 6 to 7. Weeks 3 and 4 are your build phase. Progress to a heavier band or increase reps where technique is solid, aiming for RPE 7 to 8. Weeks 5 and 6 are your progression phase. Increase resistance further and aim for the lower end of each rep range. Weeks 7 and 8 are your consolidation phase. Push working sets harder, aiming for RPE 8 to 9.

Progressive overload rule: when you can complete all sets and reps with 2 or more reps remaining in the tank, move to a heavier band or increase reps at the next session.', 'functional_strength', 'bands_only', 56, 4, 'beginner', '', '{full_body,beginner}', '2026-02-23 10:36:40.225736', 2, NULL, 'main', 'manual', NULL, '{home,travel}');


